The Gauteng Education Department is confident its systems can handle the high volume of desperate parents racing to enroll their children in Grade 1 and 8 next year. eNCA's Nqobile Madlala has this story. #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The Gauteng Education Department is confident its systems can handle the high volume of desperate parents racing to enrol their children for Grade 1 and 8 next year. Its online application system opens on Friday until 19 August. Gauteng Education MEC Panyaza Lesufi gave an update on the province's online application process. READ: 2023 school admissions | Gauteng online applications open Friday Pupils will be placed from 3 to 31 October this year. And though Lesufi admits other areas are oversubscribed, he says no child will be turned away. * eNCA's Nqobile Madlala reports. Parents/Guardians
Here’s a list of Decentralized Walk-in Centres in Ekurhuleni, Joburg, Tshwane, Sedibeng & West Rand that you can visit as an alternative to apply for Grade 1 & 8 during the #2023OnlineAdmissionsGP application period
